The paper deals with modeling the correlation between sources in distributed source coding (DSC) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes for compression suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The incorporation of an interleaver to introduce randomness in the binary domain suggests that the paper may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of multiple binary symmetric channels (BSCs) to model the correlation between continuous-valued sources suggests that the paper may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the focus on improving the efficiency of the DSC system suggests that the paper may also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
